# The browsers this library — and the Storybook that documents it — support.
#
# This floor is deliberately at or above native CSS `light-dark()` (Baseline
# widely available since 2024: Chrome/Edge 123, Firefox 120, Safari 17.5). That
# is the contract the shared M3 theme is built on: it emits every `--mat-sys-*` /
# `--ui-sys-*` role as a `light-dark()` pair and flips the whole fleet between
# schemes with a single `color-scheme` (see `src/styles/_theme.scss`). Declaring
# a floor below `light-dark()` would make that mechanism unsafe to rely on.
#
# Without any config, browserslist falls back to its default query, which still
# includes engines that predate `light-dark()` (op_mini, old Chrome, …).
#
# Note this file governs browserslist-driven tooling; it does NOT by itself set
# the Storybook preview's CSS-lowering target. Vite's Lightning CSS derives that
# from `build.cssTarget`, pinned to the same floor in `.storybook/main.ts` — see
# the comment there for why a stale target silently breaks dark mode.
